{
  "book": 20,
  "chapter": 29,
  "sections": [
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 1,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "He who is often rebuked, and hardens his neck, Will suddenly be destroyed, and that without remedy. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 1,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "He who is often rebuked, and hardens his neck, Will suddenly be destroyed, and that without remedy."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 1,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 2,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "When the righteous are in authority, the people rejoice; But when a wicked man rules, the people groan. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 2,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "When the righteous are in authority, the people rejoice; But when a wicked man rules, the people groan."
